---

🧠 LOG FETCHING MODEL (NO STREAMING)

Initial load

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --tail=<N>

Refresh

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🔄 AUTO REFRESH (STRICT RULES)

- Interval-based polling only
- Uses SAME refresh endpoint
- MUST NOT:
  - scroll UI
  - modify visible logs directly
- Only updates "pending logs"

---

🧠 LOG STATE MODEL

logs: Log[]
pendingLogs: Log[]
lastSeenTimestamp: string
newLogsCount: number
selectedProject: string
selectedDeployment: string
selectedPod: string
tailSize: number
autoRefresh: boolean

---

🔢 LOG NUMBERING

- Sequential index per session
- Continues across refresh
- Resets only on pod change

---

🟡 NEW LOGS BEHAVIOR

When refresh returns new logs:

DO NOT render immediately.

Instead:

- store in "pendingLogs"
- increment "newLogsCount"

Show UI:

+X new logs  [Show]

On click:

- merge into main logs
- re-index
- update timestamp cursor
- clear pending

---

🔍 SEARCH SYSTEM

- Instant filtering
- Regex mode supported
- Highlights matches
- Does NOT mutate log data

